description:
## Problem

Companion to maggie-ugs5 (InjectKey). tcell's SimulationScreen also has `InjectMouse(x, y int, buttons ButtonMask, mod ModMask)` for injecting mouse events directly into the event queue.

## Proposed Solution

Add a new gRPC endpoint `InjectMouse` that calls `SimulationScreen.InjectMouse()` when in test mode.

### Proto Definition

```protobuf
message InjectMouseRequest {
  SessionId session_id = 1;
  int32 x = 2;
  int32 y = 3;
  MouseButtons buttons = 4;  // PRIMARY, SECONDARY, MIDDLE, etc.
  repeated Modifier modifiers = 5;
}

message InjectMouseResponse {
  bool success = 1;
  string error = 2;
}

// In EventService
rpc InjectMouse(InjectMouseRequest) returns (InjectMouseResponse);
```

### CLI Support

```bash
# Click at coordinates
yutani inject mouse -s <session-id> --x 10 --y 5 --button PRIMARY

# Click with modifier
yutani inject mouse -s <session-id> --x 10 --y 5 --button PRIMARY --mod CTRL

# Click on a widget (resolve widget bounds first)
yutani inject click -s <session-id> -w <widget-id>
```

### Use Cases

- Testing button clicks without keyboard navigation
- Testing list/table row selection via click
- Testing drag operations
- Testing scroll wheel behavior

## Dependencies

- Depends on maggie-ugs5 (InjectKey) for shared infrastructure (IsTestMode, GetSimulationScreen, CLI inject command group)

